<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="88" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,310,400,426]" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[188,1399,447,615]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin, 2022" authorityName="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2022" box="[302,420,448,474]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[302,420,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">C. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[430,522,448,474]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from those of other congeners by their triangular-shaped PLP and cone-shaped anticlockwise directed embolus tip (
<figureCitation box="[893,1020,482,508]" captionStart="Fig 6" captionStartId="12.[189,230,1807,1833]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig 6. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus.C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. E–F. Palp. E. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. G. Epigynum. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–D = 2 mm; E–F = 0.2 mm; G = 0.1 mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Figs 6E–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1034,1109,483,509]" captionStart="Fig 7" captionStartId="13.[189,230,1829,1855]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,281,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[189,1398,266,1776]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig 7. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Palp. A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C. Epigynum ventral view. D. Vulva dorsal view. Abbreviations: AG = accessory gland; CO = copulatory opening; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; S = spermatheca; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 0.2 mm; C–D = 0.1 mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="88">7A–B</figureCitation>
). The palp of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2022" box="[1278,1398,483,509]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1398,483,509]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">C. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jastrzebski 1999" authorityName="Jastrzebski" authorityYear="1999" box="[497,795,518,544]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erus">
<emphasis box="[497,585,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">C. erus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jastrzebski P." box="[595,795,518,544]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref13287" refString="Jastrzebski P. 1999. Salticidae from the Himalaya: the genus Carrhotus Thorell 1891 (Araneae, Salticidae). Senckenbergiana Biologica 9: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1999">Jastrzebski 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; however, its PLP is relatively short, rounded and RTA is not pointed. RTA is smaller and tapered (
<figureCitation box="[745,832,553,580]" captionStart="Fig 6" captionStartId="12.[189,230,1807,1833]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig 6. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus.C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. E–F. Palp. E. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. G. Epigynum. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–D = 2 mm; E–F = 0.2 mm; G = 0.1 mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
) than in other 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1209,553,579]" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis box="[996,1116,553,579]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Carrhotus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1278,1395,553,579]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. Females are distinguished by the prominent hood at the CO and hook-shaped CD (
<figureCitation box="[1157,1287,588,614]" captionStart="Fig 7" captionStartId="13.[189,230,1829,1855]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,281,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[189,1398,266,1776]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig 7. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Palp. A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C. Epigynum ventral view. D. Vulva dorsal view. Abbreviations: AG = accessory gland; CO = copulatory opening; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; S = spermatheca; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 0.2 mm; C–D = 0.1 mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="88">Fig. 7C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
