<paragraph blockId="14.[188,1399,401,498]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
EPIGYNUM. Epigyne with a pair of copulatory ducts with a loop or flap-like structure arising from elongated pear-shaped spermathecae, whose latter part is narrowing. Accessory glands open at 3 o’clock position at narrowing anterior region of lateral walls of spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1113,471,497]" captionStart="Fig 6" captionStartId="12.[189,230,1807,1833]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig 6. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus.C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. E–F. Palp. E. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. G. Epigynum. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–D = 2 mm; E–F = 0.2 mm; G = 0.1 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Figs 6G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1126,1201,471,497]" captionStart="Fig 7" captionStartId="13.[189,230,1829,1855]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,281,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[189,1398,266,1776]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig 7. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Palp. A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C. Epigynum ventral view. D. Vulva dorsal view. Abbreviations: AG = accessory gland; CO = copulatory opening; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; S = spermatheca; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 0.2 mm; C–D = 0.1 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="92">7C–D</figureCitation>
