<paragraph blockId="14.[189,494,536,563]" box="[189,494,536,563]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,494,536,563]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,494,536,563]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1398,583,645]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
This species occurs in the mangrove forest, in the arid zone and lowland secondary rainforest of 
<collectingCountry name="Sri Lanka" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[278,365,618,644]" captionStart="Fig 17" captionStartId="28.[189,230,1982,2008]" captionTargetBox="[189,1382,719,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-115@28.[189,1397,718,1944]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig 17. Distribution of Carrhotus spp. of Sri Lanka." pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Specimens were collected by beating foliage up to a height of 
<specimenCount box="[1118,1170,618,645]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1118,1166,618,645]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
